<TITLE> Hasina meets secretaries, ministers Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina will meet with secretaries to all the ministries and divisions of the government on Sunday, cabinet secretary MA Aziz said on Saturday. She is also expected to meet with ministers and state ministers before the sitting with the secretaries in her first visit to the Secretariat in nearly seven and a half years. The cabinet secretary told bdnews24.com the prime minister would meet the ministers at 10:30am and secretaries at 11:45am. "There is a convention of holding meetings with secretaries of different ministries and divisions immediately after the new prime minister takes office," Aziz said. "The prime minister will give the top civil servants directives on different issues including usual work plans and fast implementation of ADP projects." The new head of government also get updates on the state of things from the secretaries, the cabinet secretary added. bd
